value.value: A chemical exposure (PECO:0007189) involving the application of inorganic chemical(s).
A mineral exposure (PECO:0007044) involving exposure of plant to nickel (CHEBI:28112).
An inorganic anion exposure (PECO:0001009) involving the application of phosphate (CHEBI:18367).
A mineral exposure (PECO:0007044) involving exposure of the plant(s) to mineral salts (CHEBI:24866).

definition.value: A salt (CHEBI:24866) is defined as an assembly of cations and anions. This is a genral term to include the salts of various minerals.

value.value: An inorganic anion exposure (PECO:0001009) involving the application of sulfate (CHEBI:35175).
An inorganic chemical exposure (PECO:0001004) involving the application of an anion or a mixture of anions (CHEBI:22563).

definition.value: An anion (CHEBI:22653) is defined as a monoatomic or polyatomic species having one or more elementary charges of the electron.

value.value: An organic chemical exposure (PECO:0001003) involving the application of a carbohydrate (CHEBI:16646) or mixture of carbohydrates.

definition.value: Carbohydrate (CHEBI:16646) is defined as the generic term 'carbohydrate' includes monosaccharides, oligosaccharides and polysaccharides as well as substances derived from monosaccharides by reduction of the carbonyl group (alditols), by oxidation of one or more hydroxy groups to afford the corresponding aldehydes, ketones, or carboxylic acids, or by replacement of one or more hydroxy group(s) by a hydrogen atom. Cyclitols are generally not regarded as carbohydrates.

value.value: A carbohydrate exposure (PECO:0001010) involving the application of monosaccharide(s)(CHEBI:35381).

definition.value: Monosaccharides (CHEBI:35381) are defined as polyhydroxy aldehydes H[CH(OH)]nC(=O)H or polyhydroxy ketones H-[CHOH]n-C(=O)[CHOH]m-H with three or more carbon atoms. The generic term 'monosaccharide' (as opposed to oligosaccharide or polysaccharide) denotes a single unit, without glycosidic connection to other such units. It includes aldoses, dialdoses, aldoketoses, ketoses and diketoses, as well as deoxy sugars, provided that the parent compound has a (potential) carbonyl group.

value.value: A monosaccharide exposure (PECO:0001011) involving the application of hexose (CHEBI:18133) sugar(s).

definition.value: Hexose (CHEBI:18133) is defined as any six-carbon monosaccharide which in its linear form contains either an aldehyde group at position 1 (aldohexose) or a ketone group at position 2 (ketohexose).

value.value: A hexose exposure (PECO:0001012) involving the application of glucose (CHEBI:17234).
A carbohydrate exposure (PECO:0001010) involving the application of disaccharide(s)(CHEBI:36233).

definition.value: Disaccharide (CHEBI:36233) is defined as a compound in which two monosaccharides are joined by a glycosidic bond.

value.value: A disaccharide exposure (PECO:0001014) involving the application of sucrose (CHEBI:17992).

definition.value: Sucrose (CHEBI:17992) is defined as a disaccharide formed by glucose and fructose units joined by an acetal oxygen bridge from hemiacetal of glucose to the hemiketal of the fructose.

definition.value: Parasitic wasp (or parasitoid wasp) refers to a large evolutionary grade of hymenopteran superfamilies, mainly in the Apocrita.
